---
description: General coding constraints
alwaysApply: true
---

- Give each module one responsibility.
- Keep files under approximately 250 lines and functions under approximately 40 lines; split them when they grow beyond those limits.
- Prefer explicit code and composition over magic and inheritance.
- Do not duplicate behavior, use unexplained TODOs, or combine parsing, transformation, and file writing in one module.
- Keep business logic independent of the CLI and other presentation layers.
- Add a regression test for every bug fix.
